CatDescriptText: Mrs. Janet Williams, housewife, Uptown, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column, published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 3, 1962, pg. 10  with question: "In what way do you think the successful orbiting of Col. John Glenn will aid the United States in its relationship with other countries?"  Answer reads: "Sure it will help.   It's hard to say whether Russia really succeeded before we did.  They never did prove it and we did by keeping everything out in open."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Janet Williams wearing light colored head scarf, overcoat, and gloves, standing on sidewalk, Downtown
